review.review_text: Nice food amazing place affordable rates had Oreo shake with Chicken  rolls . Staff Services up to the mark. They have nice collection of songs it was nice

We had a very exclusive dinner experience here and enjoyed it very much. After all I must say, that the service impressed me even more than the food. It was outstanding, as if they could read your mind and knew exactly what you wanted. The food was really of highest quality but it lacked a little soul. Almost too perfect in every way. Still, I would highly recommend dinner here if you can afford it (bring your savings!).

5 stars for the food and service however our evening was ruined by a table who thought that bringing a two year old out to dinner was a good idea. I will not get into their decisions but I will complain about the lack of concern by the management for damage done to the ambiance of the restaurant that was DESTROYED by the inability of the child ( it is a child) to sit through a long dinner like what is offered at 11 mad. Shame on the management who shrugged their shoulders when I expressed my displeasure. Per Se for me from now on.

Good ambience too.. As i am a foodie, i always ensure I have the best quality food. I was not disappointed and I must say it was good. Had tremendously mountain-top high expectation for this restaurant. Let me start with why the four star.

review.review_text: Experience: Exceptional ramen place with very good appetisers and one of the best ramen broths youll ever have. Tried karaka spicy which is the spicier version of akamaru modern, their most popular menu item. Also tried the shrimp hirata buns - it was good but would like to try the pork buns next time, fried shishito peppers  - nothing exceptional but a good snack, and Goma Q(cucumber with their secret sesame chili oil)-loved it. But if I had to choose one item from their menu, it has to be the ramen. The wait is upwards of an hour on weekends if you go around 7-8pm. Service was quick though.  Food: 4/5 Service: 5/5 Ambience: 5/5 Value for money: 4/5 Overall:4.5/5~5/5

review.review_text: This restaurant has stayed true to its roots for more than 100 years. Steak is always perfect. Love the spinach & original beef that just melted in my mouth. Seriously delicious. Best steak ever.

high end food. no frills restaurant. fantastic service. best steak you're ever gonna get. awesome broiled steak. need a menu? nope. steak for two. pick a side. traditional food at its best. bring cash. no credit accepted. lunch doesn't need a reservation, but be ready to wait through a line of tourists. worth every penny and minute. why not get a great old fashioned while you wait to be seated?

review.review_text: The reason I visited this place was the Pastrami Sandwich which my colleagues highly recommended. When I saw my server getting the sandwich I was a tad bit disappointed because it seemed too simple. But this was short lived and the sandwich really packed a punch and the flavors were just perfect. Totally worth it!!  I also ordered the Matzo Ball soup and the Potato Laylas both of which were also good. But the hero was definitely the Pastrami sandwich.

restaurant.name: Carmine's Italian Restaurant

location.locality_verbose: West 44th Street, Gramercy, New York City

restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 12 Midnight

review.review_text: Been there when in NY , two weeks ago just before the musical. We booked for 5:30 pm and were there at 5:35 pm (because of huge crowd in Times Square its not very easy to walk)  The lady at the front desk told us to wait 2 minutes so they can show our table. After 5mins we asked whether they forgot us. She asked to wait 2 minutes more. The restaurant is very busy just in the middle of Broadway. However, the show was at sharp 7pm ; 10mins away from the restaurant. That was the reason we booked and wanted to be seated ideally not too late.  At 5:50 pm we went back to talk to her and ask if we actually have a table or not. She was very rude and told us we came only 5 minutes ago!?! yet we are creating an issue. We should be patient and will be seated soon?   We explained that we have tickets for 7pm and also when you book restaurant you can tolerant 5-10mins maybe but not half an hour!? Also we told her that she should be more kind and explain us if there is a issue and no table available instead of telling us to wait 2minutes all the time as if we are kids. Finally we were seated at 6pm.Unfortunately we couldnt enjoy the dinner ; it was very quick. Waiters, instead, were very kind and made their best. We ended up having our pasta in doggy bag... The portions are incredibly big. One portion of pasta will be easily enough for 3 people. The best thing was artichokes. Or maybe because that was the only thing we could eat and try to enjoy:)

I had such a wonderful experience here about 2 weeks ago.  My BFF's family was in town so she arranged this dinner which I was invited to.  She mentioned the reservationist was really pleasant and had heard the food was good.  This restaurant is so comfortable and the staff were very welcoming.  The food was delicious.  The bread at the start was a focaccia and it was yummy.  Caesar salad was really big, which we split 2 of amongst us.   The meat lasagna was so terrific and fresh and one of us ordered the fried calamari, which was pretty much awesome.  My main was the penne alavodka, which I absolutely loved.

review.review_text: Im from CT, but my friends and I often come into the city on the weekend to find new spots to eat and shop. Theres one place in the East Village that is very fast and a great casual meeting place, that many have probably seen before. However, this place was new to us! I spotted them on Instagram and wanted to try it! We got the tikka fries, veggie burgers, and the fried chicken (which is gluten-free)! Healthy and affordable. Highly recommend if youre ever walking around downtown!
This Ambience has good stuff and very helpful people they helped me a lot in deciding my food menu ordered one mocktail and cocktail and mocktail I ordered mojito and it was very cold and I loved it

restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 11 PM (Mon-Sun)

review.review_text: I had one chilli potato and one tensions at hear them some stuffing was very good and also the chilli potato Vada crispy and I like the long and language Chilli potatoes here, also had one chicken burger of double size .

I was here for dinner while visiting a friend at Columbia University, it was packed but service was still very quick. Ive been to various shake shack locations across New York and the world and they had the best shack stack Ive ever had. They also had the chicken bites before any other location did. They only negative thing was that I had to make my own half and half so it tasted a little different than what I get from other shake shacks.

review.review_text: It is hard to find a restaurant that is a combination of a gorgeous space with creative and beautiful food but the Modern is one of those rare places.

Had our company Christmas party here last year and everyone is still talking about it. The food and drinks were extremely creative and well worth the price. Expect to pay for your dinner and drinks but the $ is so worth it. I've been several times before and after and I love it each and every time. The layout is very trendy and unexpected it. I think it beat TAO across the street. Hands Up!!

restaurant.name: Shake Shack

location.address: Madison Square Park, 23rd & Madison, New York 10010

restaurant.timings: 7 AM to 11 PM (Mon-Fri), 8 AM to 11 PM (Sat-Sun)

review.review_text: I love their burgers and cheese fries and 100% all-natural Vienna beef dog! Top it off with their Organic Fresh Brewed Iced Tea! Twas off the hook!  The place is inside Madison Square Park. And towering from the left is flatiron Building for the perfect view.

Felt more like a high quality fast food place. Generally don't like veggie burgers in the US but their shroom burgers were quite good. Classic strawberry shake was quite good. Best was GoT themed shake called Dragonglass shake, which was mint chocolate. Little expensive but worth the price.

Better than the classic fast food burgers - notably juicier and less gristly beef with great flavours in the smokeshack - but it got to over $8 for a very small burger, so you wonder at what point you start expecting a fancy burger. The park setting with a beer is good though and very popular in the evening.

After going to see the flatiron building we thought we would stop for a burger at Shake Shack and my oh my they are good. For a take away burger they are fresh full of flavor and delicious. If you ever come to the states please try, you wont regret it.

restaurant.name: Gramercy Tavern

location.locality_verbose: East 20th Street, Gramercy-Flatiron, New York City

restaurant.timings: 11:30 AM to 11 PM (Mon-Thu, Sun), 11:30 AM to 12 Midnight (Fri-Sat)

review.review_text: Very nice ambience and an awesome meal, was lucky enough to be there on the night that Melih Demirel Executive Chef, Frankie  Istanbul, Turkey was doing his Turkish Lamb Dish, one of the nicest meals that I have had in a week of dining in New York. Wait service was most excellent and they are a no tipping restaurant, perfect for(tight) Australians :-)

This is about the best restaurant in NYC! Impeccable service, tongue tickling tasting menu with paired wines, including a vegetarian one if you ask for it. The dessert could be made a little more exciting though!

Excellent lunch and wine package  Lovely experience in the Dining Room at the Gramercy Tavern for our final day in New York. The food and wines were truly special and the service was genuine and very attentive. They are also to be commended for having a no tipping policy. No hesitation in recommending this restaurant.
